Multiple sclerosis (MS) is an autoimmune disease that affects the central nervous system (CNS). The following list includes some possible symptoms associated with MS:
1. Vision problems - blurred vision, double vision, or loss of vision in one eye; painful eyes;
2. Muscle weakness, numbness or tingling sensations in arms legs & feet;
3. Fatigue & malaise during physical activities such as walking long distances or climbing stairs;
4. Difficulty with balance coordination & gait leading to falls risk especially when standing on tiptoes or heels;
5. Tremors trembling limbs hands/feet due to involuntary muscle contractions caused by neuron damage within the CNS;
6. Spasticity tightness rigidity making movement difficult especially after being immobile for periods at home or work;
